 for bestpractices and # Master Dashboard

## Overview
Create a comprehensive Master Dashboard for LifeOps that serves as the primary command center for multi-agent orchestration. This page delivers global search, a fast command bar, an active cronjobs snapshot, cross-module alerts, and quick-access workflows. It tightly integrates with Agent Templates & Personas, the Cronjobs system, Master Dashboard global search, and a Notifications/Alerts subsystem. The UI must be performance-oriented, highly configurable, and accessible, with strong runtime safety guarantees for all data interactions. The prompt below is designed for an AI development tool to generate code, data models, API contracts, UI components, and integration patterns that adhere to the project’s architectural goals and the mandatory runtime safety rules described in the project context.

## Page Description (Full Detail)
What this page is:
- The Master Dashboard is the single command center within LifeOps for cross-domain coordination. It provides an at-a-glance overview of global state and actionability: global search, a persistent quick command bar, a live snapshot of active cronjobs, aggregated cross-module alerts, and a set of quick-access workflows (e.g., Create Cronjob, Run Workflow, View Approvals).

Goals:
- Enable fast discovery and execution of actions across domains (Projects/Dev, Content, Finance, Health).
- Surface operational health: upcoming cron runs, last outcomes, and health indicators for active agents/workflows.
- Provide a centralized place for initiating templates/personas, workflows, approvals, and monitoring.
- Ensure high usability for power users (dense information with scannable widgets) while preserving visual clarity and responsive performance.
- Ensure robust performance through caching, indexing, and monitoring strategies; guarantee data integrity and traceability with an auditable run artifact trail.

Connected features:
- Agent Templates & Personas: Catalog of reusable agent templates and domain personas (developer triage, content writer, finance reconciler, health coach) accessible from the Master Dashboard for quick provisioning.
- Master Dashboard & Global Search: Command center with a global search/command bar and cross-module overview widgets (projects, cronjobs, agents, alerts, workflows).
- Performance & Optimization: Caching, indexing, and monitoring strategies to ensure responsive UI and reliable background processing.
- Notifications & Alerts: In-app, email, and push notifications for run outcomes, approvals, anomalies, and alerts with digesting and snoozing.
- Cronjobs Dashboard: Under the connected Cronjobs Dashboard, provide entry points, quick actions, and contextual data for cronjobs managed from Master Dashboard.

UI/UX guidance:
- Global Search: Fuzzy, cross-domain query capability with URL/actionable results; support filters by module, status, owner, and time.
- Active Cronjobs snapshot: Next run time, last outcome, health indicators, retry policy hints, and quick action controls.
- Cross-module alerts: Aggregated alert stream with prioritization, escalation path, and snooze/digest capabilities; drill-down to impacted modules.
- Quick-access workflows: Shortcuts to commonly used tasks, including creating cronjobs, launching workflows from templates, submitting approvals, and viewing recent actions.
- Overview widgets: Projects summary, publishing queue, finance snapshot, health workload balance; customizable/dockable widgets for user personalization.
- Visual style: Dark UI with dense but legible typography, high-contrast actionable elements, and restrained color accents for states.

Mandatory Coding Standards — Runtime Safety (CRITICAL):
- Supabase query results: Always use nullish coalescing — const items = data ?? [].
- Array methods: Guard against null/undefined/non-array:
  - (items ?? []).map(...)
  - Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : []
- React useState for arrays/objects: Initialize with correct type, e.g., useState< cronjob[] >([]), useState<MyItem[]>([]).
- API response shapes: Validate responses:
  - const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []
- Optional chaining: Use obj?.property?.nested for nested API results.
- Destructuring with defaults: const { items = [], count = 0 } = response ?? {}

PROJECT CONTEXT DETAILS:
- Target Page: Master Dashboard
- Target Modules/Interactions: Global search across Projects, Content, Finance, Health; agent templates and personas; cronjobs; alerts; approvals; quick actions.
- Data-sensitive: Run artifacts, inter-agent messages, and audit trails must be accessible and reversible; maintain run history, logs, diffs, and artifacts with traceability.
- No external API prerequisites for this prompt beyond internal data sources; design the backend to support future integrations.

## Components to Build
- MasterDashboardShell
  - Layout: Left navigation rail, top header with global search, center content area with widgets.
  - Data hooks: Live fetch for cronjobs, alerts, templates, and approvals; cache layers for performance.
- GlobalSearchBar
  - Features: Fuzzy search across modules; keyboard shortcuts (Cmd/Ctrl+K), results pane with categorized sections, quick actions for top hits.
  - Data: Indexed results from Projects, Cronjobs, Agents, Templates, Approvals, Alerts.
- QuickCommandBar
  - Shortcuts: Create Cronjob, Run Workflow, View Approvals, Open Templates, Clear Cache.
  - Interaction: Type-to-filter; command palette modal style with command entries.
- ActiveCronjobsSnapshot
  - Card/Panel: List next run, last outcome, schedule, retries, time until next run, health indicators.
  - Actions: Enable/disable, view details, quick edit.
- CrossModuleAlertsPanel
  - Aggregated alerts stream with severity, source module, timestamp; snooze/digest toggles; drill-down to detail pages.
- QuickAccessWorkflows
  - Tiles/quick cards for Create Cronjob, Run Workflow, Approvals, Templates, Asset actions.
- AgentTemplatesCatalog
  - Repository view with domain personas (developer triage, content writer, finance reconciler, health coach); ability to preview and instantiate templates.
