Technical details for components:
- Data-driven cards with elevation and gradient backgrounds per style guide.
- Icons: monochrome, frosted folder glyphs for app assets; use neutral highlight color #CFCFCF for icon fills with subtle top gloss.
- Charts: Minimalist, with teal, amber, purple series; tooltips with white text; gridlines at low opacity.

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Frameworks: React (with TypeScript), hook-based components, and a modular component architecture aligned to the design system.
- State management: Local component state for UI, global state for user preferences; a lightweight store (e.g., Zustand) or context-based state for cross-component communication; ensure proper typing.
- Accessibility: ARIA labels, keyboard navigation, high-contrast visuals for accessibility; focus management in dialogs and drawers.
- Performance:
  - Use caching for expensive data (cronjob lists, alerts) with time-based invalidation.
  - Lazy load widgets; render only visible sections; paginate long lists.
  - Debounce search input; use memoization for filtered results.
- Data handling safety (runtime safety rules):
  - Always initialize arrays with useState<Type[]>([]) and guard all array operations with (array ?? []).method(...) or Array.isArray(array) ? array.map(...) : [].
  - Validate and sanitize all API responses; use response?.data ?? [] patterns.
  - Use optional chaining for nested data and defaults in destructuring.
- API contracts (mocked if necessary):
  - Endpoints to fetch: cronjobs, alerts, templates, approvals, projects summary, finance snapshot, health metrics, templates catalog, user preferences.
  - Endpoints to mutate: enable/disable cronjob, create cronjob, run workflow, approve/reject actions, digest/snooze alerts.
- Data models:
  - Cronjob object: id, name, enabled, schedule, timezone, triggerType, target, inputPayload, permissions, constraints, safetyRails, retryPolicy, outputs, nextRun, lastRunResult.
  - Template/Persona: id, domain, name, description, inputSchema, previewSnippet, tags.
  - Alert: id, severity, message, sourceModule, timestamp, acknowledged, digestible, snoozedUntil.
  - Approval: id, itemType, itemId, requester, status, createdAt, dueAt.
  - RunArtifact: runId, cronjobId, status, logs, artifacts, diffs, errors, traceLink.
- Data fetching patterns:
  - Use fetch wrappers with retries and exponential backoff; guard responses with Array.isArray checks; apply data ?? [].
  - Normalize API payloads to consistent shapes before rendering.
- Security:
  - Ensure all calls are authorized; token-based authentication; role-based access for enabling cronjobs and approving actions.
  - Validate user inputs and payload structures in UI before sending to APIs.
- Validation:
  - Input fields (cron schedule, timezones, payload templates) validated on client side; server-side validation placeholders prepared for production.

### Backend
- Database layer:
  - Tables/collections for cronjobs, templates/personas, alerts, approvals, run artifacts, and related metadata.
  - Schema validations for required fields; index fields used by search (name, domain, status, nextRun, etc.).
- API endpoints:
  - GET /master-dashboard/cronjobs
  - POST /master-dashboard/cronjobs (create)
  - PATCH /master-dashboard/cronjobs/{id} (enable/disable, update)
  - GET /master-dashboard/alerts
  - POST /master-dashboard/alerts/{id}/digest (digesting)
  - POST /master-dashboard/alerts/{id}/snooze
  - GET /master-dashboard/templates
  - GET /master-dashboard/approvals
  - POST /master-dashboard/approvals/{id}/approve
  - POST /master-dashboard/approvals/{id}/reject
  - GET /master-dashboard/projects/summary
  - GET /master-dashboard/finance/snapshot
  - GET /master-dashboard/health/workload
- Business logic:
  - Cronjob scheduling engine placeholder with fields for cron expression or UI schedule builder, and timezone awareness.
  - Validation for input payloads: prompt templates, variables, scope, constraints, safety rails.
  - Audit logging for every action, including who performed it, when, and rationale.
- Caching/Indexing:
  - Implement query-level caching for frequently read data (cronjobs list, alerts, templates).
  - Index searches for global search indexing across modules.
- Security:
  - RBAC checks, permissions for cronjob actions, approvals, and template instantiation.
  - Input validation and sanitized payloads to prevent injection risks.
- Validation:
  - Validate API inputs; ensure null-safe returns; use default empty arrays when data is missing.

### Integration
- Data flow:
  - Master Dashboard pulls data from Cronjobs, Alerts, Templates/Personas, Approvals, Projects, Finance, Health modules via internal APIs.
  - Global Search aggregates results from multiple modules; results are categorized by module type.
  - Quick Actions trigger workflows or creation of cronjobs and approvals; actions are logged as RunArtifacts.
- Interactions:
  - Clicking an alert drills into the relevant module with context from the alert.
  - Creating a cronjob requires choosing a target template, input payload, constraints, safety rails, and schedule; results propagate to Cronjobs Dashboard and Master Dashboard overview.
  - Approvals queue integrates with the RunArtifact trace to present run impact and provenance.

## User Experience Flow
1. User lands on Master Dashboard; sees a global search bar, quick command bar, and a grid of overview widgets (Projects, Publishing Queue, Finance Snapshot, Health Workload).
2. User types in the Global Search; results appear in a categorized panel; user selects a hit to navigate to the targeted module or action.
3. User uses Quick Command Bar to trigger Create Cronjob, Run Workflow, or Open Templates; a command drawer/modal opens and guides through required fields.
4. User reviews Active Cronjobs Snapshot showing next run time, last outcome, and health indicators; can enable/disable or view details.
5. User checks Cross-Module Alerts panel; can digest/snooze alerts, or drill down to the source module for remediation.
6. User taps Quick Access Workflows to launch templates, approvals, or artifacts; actions generate RunArtifacts and populate the Run History.
7. User uses Overview Widgets to monitor projects, queue status, and health metrics; data refreshes in real time or near-real time via subscriptions/polling.
8. If action requires approvals, it appears in the Approvals queue with due dates; user can approve/reject; decisions propagate to the corresponding cronjob/workflow.

## Technical Specifications

Data Models:
- Cronjob
  - id: string
  - name: string
  - enabled: boolean
  - schedule: string // cron expression or UI-built schedule
  - timezone: string
  - triggerType: 'time' | 'event' | 'conditional'
  - targetId: string // agent/workflow template
  - inputPayload: object
  - permissions: { automationLevel: 'suggest-only' | 'approval-required' | 'conditional-auto' | 'bounded-autopilot' }
  - constraints: { maxActions?: number; spendLimit?: number; allowedTools?: string[] }
  - safetyRails: { confirmationsRequired?: boolean; confirmationsGiven?: boolean }
  - retryPolicy: { backoffMs?: number; maxRetries?: number; deadLetter?: string }
  - outputs: { runHistoryId?: string; logs?: string[]; artifacts?: string[] }
  - nextRun: string // ISO datetime
  - lastRunResult: string // status
- Template/Persona
  - id: string
  - domain: 'developer'|'content'|'finance'|'health'
  - name: string
  - description: string
  - inputSchema: object
  - previewSnippet: string
  - tags: string[]
- Alert
  - id: string
  - severity: 'info'|'warning'|'critical'|'error'
  - message: string
  - sourceModule: string
  - timestamp: string
  - acknowledged: boolean
  - digestible: boolean
  - snoozedUntil?: string
- Approval
  - id: string
  - itemType: string
  - itemId: string
  - requester: string
  - status: 'pending'|'approved'|'rejected'
  - createdAt: string
  - dueAt?: string
- RunArtifact
  - runId: string
  - cronjobId: string
  - status: 'pending'|'running'|'success'|'failed'
  - logs: string[]
  - artifacts: string[]
  - diffs: string[]
  - errors: string[]
  - traceLink?: string

API Endpoints:
- GET /api/master-dashboard/cronjobs
- POST /api/master-dashboard/cronjobs
- PATCH /api/master-dashboard/cronjobs/{id}
- GET /api/master-dashboard/alerts
- POST /api/master-dashboard/alerts/{id}/digest
- POST /api/master-dashboard/alerts/{id}/snooze
- GET /api/master-dashboard/templates
- GET /api/master-dashboard/approvals
- POST /api/master-dashboard/approvals/{id}/approve
- POST /api/master-dashboard/approvals/{id}/reject
- GET /api/master-dashboard/projects/summary
- GET /api/master-dashboard/finance/snapshot
- GET /api/master-dashboard/health/workload
- GET /api/master-dashboard/search?q=...
- GET /api/master-dashboard/run-artifacts/{runId}

Security & Validation:
- Authentication: JWT/OAuth token required for all endpoints; RBAC restrictions for cronjob creation/enable/disable, approvals, and template usage.
- Input validation: All POST/PATCH requests validated server-side; client-side validations implemented with user-friendly feedback.
- Data integrity: Use server-side validation for required fields; audit logs stored with timestamp and user.

Validation Rules:
- Null-safe returns: Use data ?? [] in responses; guard for missing fields.
- Array operations guarded: (items ?? []).map(...) or Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : [].
- Respond with consistent shapes: Ensure responses always include the expected keys with safe defaults.

Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Master Dashboard loads with all widgets rendering correctly using safe defaults (no null crashes).
- [ ] Global search returns results across at least 4 modules with category sections and actionable items; results use fuzzy matching and keyboard navigation.
- [ ] Active Cronjobs Snapshot shows next run, last outcome, and a functional enable/disable toggle; bulk actions supported via a selection mechanism.
- [ ] Alerts panel displays aggregated alerts with severity indicators, snooze/digest options, and drill-down links to source modules.
- [ ] Templates/ Personas catalog is searchable and instantiates templates into a new cronjob or workflow when selected.
- [ ] Approvals queue supports approve/reject actions; due dates and requester attribution visible; actions trigger corresponding cronjob/workflow changes.
- [ ] Performance: Dashboard uses caching for cronjobs, alerts, and templates; data refreshes with minimal latency; re-renders optimized to avoid unnecessary updates.
- [ ] Accessibility: All interactive controls accessible via keyboard; ARIA labels provided; color contrast meets WCAG standards.
- [ ] Security: Unauthorized actions are rejected with proper error codes; RBAC enforced server-side; sensitive fields sanitized.

UI/UX Guidelines
Apply the project's design system:
- Follow the color palette, typography, and layout guidelines provided.
- Use dark surfaces with subtle borders; panels with rounded corners; consistent card elevation and hover states.
- Use the accent color (#FF3B30) sparingly for critical states (active alerts, destructive actions).
- Keep typography hierarchy consistent: headings (20–28px, 600–700), card titles (14–16px, 500–600), body text (12–14px, 400).
- Baseline grid: 8px with consistent multiples; left sidebar width approximately 220–260px; header height 56–64px.
- Spacing: Card paddings 16–20px; widget gaps 16–24px; gutters between sidebar and content.

Visual Style
- Maintain the exact color tokens and naming from the provided Visual Style section.
- Card design: dark elevated cards with top gloss, gradient backgrounds (#0B0B0C → #151718), subtle borders (#FFFFFF33) and drop shadows.
- Navigation: left rail with collapsible sections; active state uses a vertical accent pill in #FF3B30.
- Data visualization: minimalistic charts using teal #00C2A8, amber #FFB020, purple #8B5CF6; contrast against dark theme; tooltips with white text.
- Interactive elements: consistent button styles, toggles, chips, and badges, with hover/focus states that align to the design system.

Connected Pages
- Cronjobs Dashboard: The Master Dashboard should link to the Cronjobs Dashboard for deeper management; provide contextual breadcrumbs and quick-create actions.

Connected Features
- Agent Templates & Personas
- Master Dashboard & Global Search
- Performance & Optimization
- Notifications & Alerts
- Cronjobs Dashboard

Note for AI development tool usage
- Implement with a modular, scalable architecture that can be extended for additional modules.
- Ensure all components are strongly typed (TypeScript) and have clear prop contracts.
- Build accessible, keyboard-navigable widgets.
- Provide mock data schemas and example JSON payloads in code comments for testing where real APIs are not yet available.
- Include unit tests for critical data transformation paths and UI interaction handlers, especially for null-safe data handling and guarded array operations.

This prompt provides a complete blueprint for building the Master Dashboard with its integrated features, ensuring runtime safety, design consistency, and scalable architecture. If you’d like, I can generate concrete starter files (TypeScript React components, mock API services, and a minimal backend skeleton) that adhere to these specifications. for style.

CRITICAL DESIGN REQUIREMENTS:
- You MUST follow ALL design principles and patterns specified in the Design Reference above
- Do NOT deviate from the design specifications without explicit user permission
- Implement ALL visual design elements (colors, typography, spacing, shadows, animations) as specified
- Follow the layout patterns and component designs exactly as documented
- Ensure all interactions and micro-animations match the reference specifications

CRITICAL TECHNICAL REQUIREMENTS:
- React 18.3.1, React Router 6.30.1
- Tailwind CSS v3 with tailwind.config.js and custom keyframes
- @tailwindcss/typography plugin for rich text content
- Tailwind CSS animations (NOT Motion library or framer-motion)
- Sonner for toasts
- Recharts for data visualization
- Native fetch() with API utilities in src/lib/api.ts
- Design system with CSS custom properties
- Use RGB color values for theming
