# Master Dashboard

## Overview
Create a comprehensive Master Dashboard for LifeOps that serves as the primary command center for multi-agent orchestration. This page delivers global search, a fast command bar, an active cronjobs snapshot, cross-module alerts, and quick-access workflows. It tightly integrates with Agent Templates & Personas, the Cronjobs system, Master Dashboard global search, and a Notifications/Alerts subsystem. The UI must be performance-oriented, highly configurable, and accessible, with strong runtime safety guarantees for all data interactions. The prompt below is designed for an AI development tool to generate code, data models, API contracts, UI components, and integration patterns that adhere to the project’s architectural goals and the mandatory runtime safety rules described in the project context.

## Page Description (Full Detail)
What this page is:
- The Master Dashboard is the single command center within LifeOps for cross-domain coordination. It provides an at-a-glance overview of global state and actionability: global search, a persistent quick command bar, a live snapshot of active cronjobs, aggregated cross-module alerts, and a set of quick-access workflows (e.g., Create Cronjob, Run Workflow, View Approvals).

Goals:
- Enable fast discovery and execution of actions across domains (Projects/Dev, Content, Finance, Health).
- Surface operational health: upcoming cron runs, last outcomes, and health indicators for active agents/workflows.
- Provide a centralized place for initiating templates/personas, workflows, approvals, and monitoring.
- Ensure high usability for power users (dense information with scannable widgets) while preserving visual clarity and responsive performance.
- Ensure robust performance through caching, indexing, and monitoring strategies; guarantee data integrity and traceability with an auditable run artifact trail.

Connected features:
- Agent Templates & Personas: Catalog of reusable agent templates and domain personas (developer triage, content writer, finance reconciler, health coach) accessible from the Master Dashboard for quick provisioning.
- Master Dashboard & Global Search: Command center with a global search/command bar and cross-module overview widgets (projects, cronjobs, agents, alerts, workflows).
- Performance & Optimization: Caching, indexing, and monitoring strategies to ensure responsive UI and reliable background processing.
- Notifications & Alerts: In-app, email, and push notifications for run outcomes, approvals, anomalies, and alerts with digesting and snoozing.
- Cronjobs Dashboard: Under the connected Cronjobs Dashboard, provide entry points, quick actions, and contextual data for cronjobs managed from Master Dashboard.

